Text.Value: That depends. What are you offering me?
Aye, and I'm grateful. Baldur's Gate was the last city along the coast that we hadn't quite put our bootprint on.
I did.
I'm still not entirely clear what I get out of this deal.
Aye, not ideal. But we don't plan on going along with that - only on taking the opportunity this whole situation offers.
Zhentarim! Anyone who isn't us, dies!

EditorData.NodeContext: Shouting to her troops to launch an attack

Text.Value: The Zhentarim have been trying to crack Baldur's Gate for years, but Nine-Fingers' grip has been too strong. And look what it's come to.
Nine-Fingers is done. My Zhentarim stand ready to purge this place of everyone loyal to her.
Then look no further. The Zhentarim can protect the city - but only with Nine-Fingers out of the way.
What now?
You made it out of the sewers, I see. Cool your heels a moment, and let's talk.
But don't worry. We'll be at your back when it comes time to boot the Absolute out.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'Sword captain' is a reference to herself - a faux-humble 'yours truly', as she's sure she'll get a promotion

Text.Value: The Zhentarim will be busy putting order on this place for a while. But when you call for us, we'll come.
All right. Let's deal with Nine-Fingers.
I'm loyal to whoever can help me save this city.
A Guild under our control can do what Nine-Fingers failed to - drive the Absolute out of the city, once and for all.
Might be I'll even be flaunting a shiny new rank. I just handed my superiors quite the catch.
Most of the time.

EditorData.NodeContext: Faux-formality, with a little bow. She does mean it, but she's toying with us a little bit - we've just seen firsthand that she has no problem going back on her word.

Text.Value: Besides that dragon's hoard you got from the Counting House?
New coat of paint, I think. Then we introduce ourselves to the local vermin - let them know there's been a change of management.
That was an unfortunate bit of business - but you handled yourself well. My thanks.
Why does the Zhentarim care so much about Baldur's Gate?
So all I need to know is - does that include you, or not?
Leave.
Hah. They all did the same or worse - that's how they got to be my superiors.
We're here to stay, now. And when the battle-horns start blowing, you'll see we're as good as our word.
Why are the Zhentarim working for the cult? They want everyone dead.
Could've just kept things simple, mate. But fine - have it your way. You're just another corpse to step over.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sighing, tired - not bothered we're betraying her, just inconvenienced at the extra work

Text.Value: A better ally than the one you've got in Nine-Fingers.
I've seen enough to know you want the Absolute booted out of the city - same as I do. No reason we can't work together.
Simple enough - because it wasn't ours. Couldn't be, so long as Nine-Fingers was around.
Whatever you think you heard, whatever you're here to do - cool your heels a moment. Let's talk.

EditorData.NodeContext: Non-chalant - confident she can still turn this to her advantage.

Text.Value: Whiff of the sewers about you. You're the one eavesdropped on my private business dealings, I suppose?

EditorData.NodeContext: Sizing us up - knows we saw her in a compromising situation, taking money to betray Nine-Fingers
EditorData.logicalname: ROAH DIDN'T SEE US AT THE CISTERN

Text.Value: Now the Guild can become a Zhent operation - and we'll have your back when the battle-horns start blowing. I'm as good as my word.
Enough talking. Get out of my way, or die.
Don't thank me too soon. This isn't your office - it's mine.
TO ARMS, ZHENTARIM - THE GUILD IS OURS FOR THE TAKING!

EditorData.NodeContext: Shouting to her troops to launch an attack

Text.Value: You don't know good sense when you hear it. But fine - have it your way.
Her Guild is disorganised. Undisciplined. The cult broke them in a matter of days, while my Zhentarim still stand strong.
You're not talking me into anything. Get out of my way, or die.
Do you know - it's a genuine pleasure to deal with someone with a bit of sense in their head.
Not the fanciest office I've ever had, but it'll do.
Attack her.
And you only had to collaborate with a death-cult to do it. Your superiors won't mind?

Synopsis: Boss Friol is a possible leader of the Zhentarim in BG - she attempts to use the cult crisis to supplant Nine-Fingers and her Guild. The player can aid or thwart her.
